---
---

<section class="section section-alt" id="providers">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <p class="section-label">AI providers</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Seven providers, one interface</h2>
    <p class="section-desc-sm">
      Select a provider and model from the settings panel. API keys are stored locally in browser
      storage — nothing is proxied or logged. Switch at any time without leaving the page.
    </p>

    <div class="providers-grid">

      <div class="provider-card">
        <div class="provider-header">
          <span class="provider-name">Google AI Studio</span>
          <span class="provider-tag">API Key</span>
        </div>
        <p class="provider-desc">Direct access to Gemini models via a free-tier API key. The default provider out of the box.</p>
        <div class="provider-models">
          <span class="model-chip">gemini-2.5-flash</span>
          <span class="model-chip">gemini-2.0-flash</span>
          <span class="model-chip">gemini-1.5-pro</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="provider-card">
        <div class="provider-header">
          <span class="provider-name">Vertex AI</span>
          <span class="provider-tag">API Key</span>
        </div>
        <p class="provider-desc">Google Cloud's enterprise Gemini endpoint. Requires a Vertex AI API token.</p>
        <div class="provider-models">
          <span class="model-chip">gemini-2.5-flash</span>
          <span class="model-chip">gemini-2.0-flash</span>
          <span class="model-chip">gemini-1.5-pro</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="provider-card">
        <div class="provider-header">
          <span class="provider-name">OpenAI</span>
          <span class="provider-tag">API Key</span>
        </div>
        <p class="provider-desc">GPT models via the standard OpenAI chat completions API. Supports vision for image analysis.</p>
        <div class="provider-models">
          <span class="model-chip">gpt-4o</span>
          <span class="model-chip">gpt-4o-mini</span>
          <span class="model-chip">o3-mini</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="provider-card">
        <div class="provider-header">
          <span class="provider-name">Anthropic</span>
          <span class="provider-tag">API Key</span>
        </div>
        <p class="provider-desc">Claude models with strong reasoning and long-context support. Vision-capable for image input.</p>
        <div class="provider-models">
          <span class="model-chip">claude-opus-4-6</span>
          <span class="model-chip">claude-sonnet-4-6</span>
          <span class="model-chip">claude-haiku-4-5</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="provider-card">
        <div class="provider-header">
          <span class="provider-name">OpenRouter</span>
          <span class="provider-tag">API Key</span>
        </div>
        <p class="provider-desc">Single API key with access to hundreds of models across providers. Useful for comparing outputs.</p>
        <div class="provider-models">
          <span class="model-chip">any model</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="provider-card">
        <div class="provider-header">
          <span class="provider-name">Grok</span>
          <span class="provider-tag">API Key</span>
        </div>
        <p class="provider-desc">xAI's Grok models, compatible with the OpenAI API schema. Vision support included.</p>
        <div class="provider-models">
          <span class="model-chip">grok-3</span>
          <span class="model-chip">grok-3-mini</span>
          <span class="model-chip">grok-2-vision</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="provider-card provider-card-local">
        <div class="provider-header">
          <span class="provider-name">OpenCode</span>
          <span class="provider-tag provider-tag-local">Local</span>
        </div>
        <p class="provider-desc">Connect to a self-hosted OpenCode server running locally or on your network. Configure the URL and optional password in settings — models are fetched dynamically.</p>
        <div class="provider-models">
          <span class="model-chip">dynamic from server</span>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .providers-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 16px;
    margin-top: 8px;
  }

  /* Make last card (OpenCode) span full row on its own if grid has leftover */
  .provider-card-local {
    grid-column: span 1;
  }

  .provider-card {
    padding: 18px 20px;
    border: 1px solid #e4e4e7;
    border-radius: 10px;
    background: #fff;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 10px;
  }

  .provider-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 8px;
  }

  .provider-name {
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #18181b;
  }

  .provider-tag {
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 500;
    background: #f4f4f5;
    border: 1px solid #e4e4e7;
    color: #71717a;
    padding: 2px 7px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .provider-tag-local {
    background: #fef9c3;
    border-color: #fde68a;
    color: #92400e;
  }

  .provider-desc {
    font-size: 12px;
    color: #71717a;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .provider-models {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 6px;
    margin-top: 2px;
  }

  .model-chip {
    font-size: 10px;
    font-family: ui-monospace, "SF Mono", "Fira Code", monospace;
    background: #f4f4f5;
    color: #52525b;
    padding: 2px 8px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    border: 1px solid #e4e4e7;
  }

  @media (max-width: 960px) {
    .providers-grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); }
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .providers-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
